title: Dental therapists could be allowed to do tooth extractions
text: show ad Would you let someone who's not a dentist pull your teeth? Several states considering allowing 'dental therapists' to do so Several states are considering bills that would create a new midlevel position in dentistry called dental therapists or advanced dental hygiene practitioners They would perform common procedures such as filling cavities or pulling teeth More complex procedures would still be left with dentists Published: 06:28 GMT, 16 February 2017 | Updated: 18:32 GMT, 16 February 2017 73 shares
